      "raw_text": "INDIANAPOLIS, Oct lot is\nannounced here today that the next\nissue of the Mine Workers Journal\nwill contain an official statement\nthat John Mitchell will not be a\ncandidate for reelection as presi-\ndent OF the United Mine Workers.\nHe will retire from the organization\nentirely.\n\n\nVice President T. L. Lewis is a\ncandidate to succeed Mitchell.\nMitchell and Lewis differ on the\ntreatment of labor troubles.\n\n\n1t is predicted that If Lewis Is\nelected he will advocate great\ncoal strike. Lewis counselled a\nstrike during the last two confer\nences between the men and opera\ntors. Mitchell says i'll health is\nthe cause of his action."
    }
